  "mixStrategy": "SLEEP LATIN LULLABY \u2014 Andalusian Cadence in Am (i\u2192bVII\u2192bVI\u2192V)\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION:\n- BASS (Electric Bass, 100-300Hz, MIDI 33-48): Ultra-slow tumbao-inspired roots. Plays chord roots A, G, F, E with gentle syncopated anticipations. Long sustains (4-8s) with very low velocity (25-45). Provides the warm harmonic foundation without any rhythmic aggression.\n- CHORDS (Piano, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 48-67): Dreamy montuno fragments \u2014 not full rapid-fire montuno but slow, arpeggiated chord voicings that hint at the Latin harmonic language. Soft broken chords with long sustains. Each chord change uses open voicings (root-5th-3rd-7th spread) to create warmth. Velocity 25-45.\n- MELODY (Flute, 1-8kHz, MIDI 64-79): Gentle, breathing melodic fragments in A harmonic minor. Sparse phrases with long notes that trace the chord tones on strong beats (A over Am, G over G, F over F, E/G# over E). Occasional ornamental passing tones (B, D, G#) for Latin color. Velocity 25-50. Lots of space and silence between phrases.\n\nNO DRUMS \u2014 Sleep mode eliminates all percussion.\n\nHARMONIC PLAN (each chord = ~5.6s = ~4.5 beats at 48 BPM):\nCycle 1 (0-22.5s): Am \u2192 G \u2192 F \u2192 E7 (energy 0.3\u21920.4\u21920.5\u21920.5)\nCycle 2 (22.5-45s): Am \u2192 G \u2192 F \u2192 E7 (energy 0.4\u21920.4\u21920.3\u21920.3)\n\nENERGY ARC: Starts hushed (vel ~25-30), gently swells to mid-section (vel ~40-50), then fades back to near-silence (vel ~25-30). The piece breathes like a sleeping body \u2014 slow inhale, slow exhale.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Even in sleep mode, subtle syncopated anticipations remain \u2014 bass notes arrive just slightly before chord changes (by ~0.3s), giving a ghostly echo of clave feel. Melody phrases float above with gentle rubato-like spacing. Chords provide slow broken arpeggios that fill the harmonic middle without competing.\n\nCOHESION: All three tracks move through the same Am\u2192G\u2192F\u2192E progression simultaneously. Bass provides roots, piano provides harmonic color, flute sings the top voice. Together they create a warm, enveloping Latin lullaby.",
